records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tamara Tanika Cole in court, in custody.  Attorney Haley E Wentz in court for Tamara Tanika Cole.  Prosecuting attorney Claire E Zyber in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Return on Doctor's Report review hearing. State and Defense have received and reviewed the report.  No challenges to the Report.  Court finds the defendant is competent to proceed and reinstates the proceedings. All bail conditions remain the same.  Attorney Wentz is new to the case and is requesting a status conference.  Case is adjourned to 12-6-22 at 1:30 pm for status conference.
This hearing may be streamed live on DAcast at the discretion of the Court:
https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/d84cd54a-763c-3a58-15a9-b84acf306616
Status conference scheduled for December 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Case is scheduled for a return on doctor's report/ review hearing on 10-31-22 at 8:30 am.  Parties are notified of the hearing via email.
Order For Immediate Transfer, signed and filed.

Defendant Tamara Tanika Cole in court with attorney Colleen Cullen.  Defendant Tamara Tanika Cole in custody.  Jacob A. Maule appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Tamara Tanika Cole appeared by video means with Attorney.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.  
Case in court for return on doctors report.   Court reviews doctor's report with the parties.  State, defense counsel and defendant are not challenging the findings of the doctor's report.  Court finds the defendant lacks substantial capacity to understand court proceedings or to assist in his own defense.  Court orders proceedings suspended.    Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame.  The Court further authorized DHS to administer medications or treatment to the defendant.  Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department for transportation to the designated facility FORTHWITH.  Order of Commitment signed and filed.  Case adjourned, Br. 10.  Review hearing scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Colleen Cullen in court, defendant Tamara Tanika Cole not in court, in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Case set for a preliminary hearing. Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed. Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for August 9, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with MSC (07/31/1968)
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 4.  Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Tamara Tanika Cole in court with attorney Michael J Cerniglia.  Defendant Tamara Tanika Cole in custody.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Havas, Branch 10.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing. Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count 1.
